🔥 Tier 1 — MUST ADD (game will feel incomplete without these)
1️⃣ Supply / Connection Rules (biggest impact, low complexity)
Problem now

Isolated tiles still generate full value

You can “snake” across the map with no downside

Add this rule

Only tiles connected to HQ generate gold & barracks army

Disconnected territory:

still exists

still defendable

but produces nothing

Why this is huge

Cutting territory becomes a valid strategy

Frontlines matter

Forts gain strategic value

Comebacks become possible

Implementation hint (not code yet)

Flood-fill from HQ per player

Mark connected tiles

Count only connected ones in tick()

This alone will double strategic depth.

2️⃣ Fog of War (partial, not full)
Simple version

You only see:

tiles you own

tiles adjacent to owned tiles

Everything else:

rendered dark / unknown

still exists on server

Why this matters

Prevents perfect information

Encourages scouting

Makes surprise attacks possible

Adds tension without complexity

Important

Fog of war is client-side rendering only.
Server stays fully authoritative.

3️⃣ Capture Cooldown / Fatigue
Problem now

A player with high army can steamroll instantly

Add

After capturing a tile, player gets a short capture cooldown
or
Capturing costs more army if done repeatedly in short time

Example:

First capture: normal

Second within 3s: +20% cost

Third: +40%

Result

Prevents spam

Makes timing important

Gives defenders breathing room

